d Monteverdi; in a religious allegorical play by Calderon; and in the writings of Spenser, Milton, and Bacon. The Orpheus myth has been crucial in the defining of a culture. Its history demonstrates effectively the persistence and plasticity of myth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Folklore & Mythology.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, W.S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrwin, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeón, Pedro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGee, Timothy J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Emmet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScavizzi, Giuseppe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVicari, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarden, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarden, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757980740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487579807423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487579807.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK